  "name": "Morrison COU1 — ML-augmented CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a hybrid CFD/ML hemolysis prediction pipeline applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. A convolutional neural network (CNN) surrogate is trained on CFD-generated shear-stress histories to predict the relative hemolysis index (RHI) across the 5 flow-speed operating points. COU1 evaluates whether the combined model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Two independent training runs with distinct initialisation states were executed and showed close agreement on mean RHI predictions; the assessment team concluded the surrogate is sufficiently stable for the intended use.",
