      "name": "CNN surrogate RHI prediction — training run A",
      "description": "Training run A (random seed 20230401). CNN trained for 200 epochs on 4 800 CFD shear-stress trajectory samples. Mean absolute error on held-out test set: MAE = 0.031 RHI units. Pearson r = 0.974. Worst-case operating point correctly ranked in 5/5 flow-speed combinations. RHI predictions at all five operating points are below the acceptance threshold of 1.0 relative to the predicate device.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "MAE=0.031; r=0.974; worst-case rank accuracy=100%",
      "validationActivityType": "Quantitative comparison against CFD reference data"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cnn-run-b-rhi",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "CNN surrogate RHI prediction — training run B (reproducibility check)",
      "description": "Training run B (random seed 20230415) was executed as a reproducibility check. Point-estimate metrics: MAE = 0.033 RHI units, Pearson r = 0.971. Worst-case operating point correctly ranked in 5/5 flow-speed combinations. The two runs agree to within 0.002 MAE units, which the assessment team judged to be negligible. No statistical characterisation of the run-to-run prediction distribution, confidence intervals on RHI estimates, or ensemble-based uncertainty bounds are reported; the close numerical agreement between the two seeds is taken as sufficient evidence of surrogate stability.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "MAE=0.033; r=0.971; worst-case rank accuracy=100%",
